More of a style question, but is there a problem with doing the following?

``` ruby
def self.next_id
  synchronize {
    @id ||= 0
    @id += 1
  }
end
```

Just seems kinda clunky using the extra variable, when `@id = id + 1` and `@id += 1` will both return the new value of `@id`.

